3.1. Income Breakdown

Tennis stars’ income includes: 

• prize money from the tournaments

• sponsorship contracts with equipment and apparel producers (Quiaodan, Yonex, Uniqlo, Head, Wilson, 
Babolat, Adidas, Nike etc.)

• general advertising contracts (Evian, Lotto, Mercedes, Porsche, Tag Heuer etc.)

• appearance fees (less prestigious tournaments pay stars for mere participation)

• licensing their image and name (to games, clothing lines, perfumes)

• exhibition fees

3.2. Prize Money

Players’ career prize income differs depending on their ‘league’. 

• A superstar can be expected to earn north of $60 million in prize money alone over the course of their career. 
Roger Federer earned $104 million5 in prize money over his career. Serena Williams earned $84.4 million6� 

• A player with 1-5 tournament victories usually earns $5-9 million. French Sebastien Grosjean (4 titles) earned 
$8.1 million7, and Australian Kevin Anderson (3 titles) earned $7.8 million8�

• A low-ranked player isn’t likely to earn more than $1 million, e.g. Chinese Yifan Xu (433 rank) has earned 
$0.98M9�

